Class VP_Center

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class VP_Center
extends javafx.scene.layout.StackPane
    The center is the center of the main BorderPane layout. The center extends StackPane, where each layer of the StackPane corresponds to a wizard page. Some wizard pages may only be accessible under certain conditions.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • build

        protected void build()
        Builds the GUI center which holds most of the content. Called in a task, to build in the background. The center extends StackPane, where each layer is an individual page.
        • Layer 0 = Login Screen
        • Layer 1 = Reset Password Screen
        • Layer 2 = Registration Screen
        • Layer 3 = Overview Screen
        • Layer 4 = Personal Information Screen
        • Layer 5 = Business Card Screen
        • Layer 6 = Cover Letters List Screen
        • Layer 7 = Cover Letter Edit Screen
        • Layer 8 = Themes List Screen Screen
        • Layer 9 = Custom Theme Screen
        • Layer 10 = Distribute Screen
        • Layer 11 = Resume Status Screen
        • Layer 12 = Resume Objective Screen
        • Layer 13 = Resume Education Screen
        • Layer 14 = Resume Experience Screen
        • Layer 15 = Resume Achievements Screen
        • Layer 16 = Resume Community Screen
        • Layer 17 = Resume Qualifications Screen
        • Layer 18 = Resume Highlights Screen
        • Layer 19 = Resume Languages Screen
        • Layer 20 = Resume Software Screen
        • Layer 21 = Resume References Screen
        • Layer 22 = Change Password Screen
        Since:
        1.0

      • showScreen

        protected void showScreen(int screenNumber,
                          double position)
        Makes all center StackPane levels invisible except for the desired one.
        Parameters:
        screenNumber - The desired StackPane level to show.
        position - The scroll position on the selected screen.
        Since:
        1.0
